---
description: Use TSS for compact terminal output when exact raw output is not required.
alwaysApply: true
---

Prefer `TSS_AGENT=cursor tss run -- <command>` for terminal commands that produce large human-readable output. Do not use TSS for structured output, patches, redirected or piped commands, or any command where exact stdout/stderr is required. If TSS reports omitted output, inspect it with `tss raw <id>`.

This rule is instruction-only. Cursor terminal commands are not automatically rewritten by TSS.

For delegated or sub-agent shells, use:

```bash
TSS_AGENT=cursor TSS_SUBAGENT=1 tss run -- <command>
```
